# NHIS portal product context

This app is **not** a general clinic or hospital appointment system.

It mirrors government service portals such as [Ghana Passport Application](https://passport.mfa.gov.gh/): citizens **book a slot at an NHIA service centre** to complete **NHIS membership services**.

## Core user journeys

1. **New NHIS registration** — first-time enrollment; user receives NHIS number after verification.
2. **NHIS renewal** — existing members renew coverage at a centre.
3. **Book a centre visit** — pick service type (new vs renewal), date, and time slot (subject to admin availability rules).
4. **Track bookings** — view upcoming centre appointments and status.

## Terminology (prefer in UI and docs)

| Use | Avoid |
|-----|--------|
| NHIS registration / renewal | General consultation, health visit |
| Service centre appointment | Doctor visit, clinic booking |
| Book a centre slot | Book appointment (alone, without context) |
| Application / service type | Reason for visit (medical) |

## Technical notes

- Appointment records include `serviceType`: `new_registration` | `renewal`.
- Admin **Availability** controls which calendar dates are open or closed for bookings.
- OTP + account registration are the digital front door; the in-person step happens at the booked slot.

When adding features, ask: “Does this match passport-style **service booking + application tracking**, not hospital scheduling?”
